{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Simisear}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=513|prev=Pansear|nextnum=515|next=Panpour|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Simisear\n|jname=バオッキー\n|jtranslit=Baokkī\n|tmname=Baokkie\n|category=Ember\n|ndex=514\n|udex=020\n|u2dex=040\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=032\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fire\n|height-ftin=3\'03"\n|height-m=1.0\n|weight-lbs=61.7\n|weight-kg=28.0\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Gluttony\n|abilityd=Blaze\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|expyield=174\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=31\n|color=Red\n|catchrate=75\n|body=06\n|evtotal=2\n|evsp=2\n|pokefordex=simisear\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Simisear\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'バオッキー\'\'\' \'\'Baokkie\'\') is a {{type|Fire}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s from {{p|Pansear}} when exposed to a [[Fire Stone]].\n\n==Biology==\nSimisear is a simian Pokémon that is primarily red. Its ears are broad with orange insides, and it has oval eyes and a small black nose. It has a swirled, flame-like tuft on its head with a smaller tuft on either side of it. Simisear has white shoulder ruffs; and a cream-colored face, chest, fingers, and toes. Its hands have five fingers, and its feet have three toes. Its fluffy, swirled tail resembles a flame. There is a flame flickering inside its body, which it fuels with sweet foods. It is also capable of scattering embers from its tail and the tufts on its head.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Simisear anime.png|thumb|250px|left|Simisear in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nSimisear debuted in \'\'[[BW025|Emolga and the New Volt Switch!]]\'\'. It was knocked out of a tree by a group of {{p|Watchog}} protecting an apple tree. As a result, it took its anger out on {{TP|Iris|Emolga}}, {{TP|Iris|Axew}}, and {{AP|Oshawott}}, but eventually calmed down when the former and {{AP|Snivy}} saved it from a falling boulder.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Simisear briefly appeared in \'\'[[BW071|Search for the Clubultimate!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Getty]]. It participated in a match against Betty\'s {{p|Simipour}} during the [[Clubsplosion]] tournament, but it was defeated.\n\nA Simisear appeared in \'\'[[XY021|A PokéVision of Things to Come!]]\'\'.\n\nA Simisear appeared in \'\'[[XY026|A Battle by Any Other Name!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Simisear appeared in \'\'[[XY080|Performing with Fiery Charm!]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW025|Simisear|Ash\'s Pokédex|Simisear, the Ember Pokémon and the [[Evolution|evolved]] form of {{p|Pansear}}. Simisear loves to eat sweets, which sustain the fire that burns inside its body.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Chili Simisear Adventures.png|thumb|left|115px|Simisear in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Chili\'s Pansear|Chili\'s Simisear}}\nIn [[Pokémon Adventures]], [[Chili]]\'s Pansear evolves into Simisear by being exposed to a [[Fire Stone]] during the brothers\' fight with the [[Shadow Triad]] in \'\'[[PS519|Something Suspicious]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Simisear (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Fire}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=020|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=040|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=White|entry=A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=